#. <section class="sutta" id="sn12.24"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn12.24:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 12"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 12"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn12.24:0.2"
msgid "3. Dasabalavagga"
msgstr "3. The Ten Powers"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn12.24:0.3"
msgid "24. Aññatitthiyasutta"
msgstr "24. Followers of Other Paths"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn12.24:1.1"
msgid "Rājagahe viharati veḷuvane."
msgstr "Near Rājagaha, in the Bamboo Grove."

msgctxt "sn12.24:1.2"
msgid ""
"Atha kho āyasmā sāriputto pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya "
"rājagahaṃ piṇḍāya pāvisi."
msgstr ""
"Then Venerable Sāriputta robed up in the morning and, taking his bowl and "
"robe, entered Rājagaha for alms."

msgctxt "sn12.24:1.3"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmato sāriputtassa etadahosi:"
msgstr "Then he thought:"

msgctxt "sn12.24:1.4"
msgid "“atippago kho tāva rājagahe piṇḍāya carituṃ."
msgstr "“It’s too early to wander for alms in Rājagaha."

msgctxt "sn12.24:1.5"
msgid ""
"Yannūnāhaṃ yena aññatitthiyānaṃ paribbājakānaṃ ārāmo tenupasaṅkameyyan”ti."
msgstr ""
"Why don’t I go to the monastery of the wanderers who follow other paths?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi2.33"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn12.24:2.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho āyasmā sāriputto yena aññatitthiyānaṃ paribbājakānaṃ ārāmo "
"tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā tehi aññatitthiyehi paribbājakehi saddhiṃ "
"sammodi."
msgstr ""
"Then he went to the monastery of the wanderers who follow other paths, and "
"exchanged greetings with the wanderers there."

msgctxt "sn12.24:2.2"
msgid ""
"Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ "
"nisinnaṃ kho āyasmantaṃ sāriputtaṃ te aññatitthiyā paribbājakā etadavocuṃ:"
msgstr ""
"When the greetings and polite conversation were over, he sat down to one "
"side. The wanderers said to him:"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn12.24:3.1"
msgid ""
"“Santāvuso sāriputta, eke samaṇabrāhmaṇā kammavādā sayaṃkataṃ dukkhaṃ "
"paññapenti."
msgstr ""
"“Reverend Sāriputta, there are ascetics and brahmins who teach the efficacy "
"of deeds. Some of them declare that suffering is made by oneself."

msgctxt "sn12.24:3.2"
msgid ""
"Santi panāvuso sāriputta, eke samaṇabrāhmaṇā kammavādā paraṃkataṃ dukkhaṃ "
"paññapenti."
msgstr "Some of them declare that suffering is made by another."

msgctxt "sn12.24:3.3"
msgid ""
"Santāvuso sāriputta, eke samaṇabrāhmaṇā kammavādā sayaṃkatañca paraṃkatañca "
"dukkhaṃ paññapenti."
msgstr ""
"Some of them declare that suffering is made by both oneself and another."

msgctxt "sn12.24:3.4"
msgid ""
"Santi panāvuso sāriputta, eke samaṇabrāhmaṇā kammavādā asayaṃkāraṃ "
"aparaṅkāraṃ adhiccasamuppannaṃ dukkhaṃ paññapenti."
msgstr ""
"Some of them declare that suffering arises by chance, not made by oneself or "
"another."

msgctxt "sn12.24:3.5"
msgid "Idha, panāvuso sāriputta, samaṇo gotamo kiṃvādī kimakkhāyī?"
msgstr "What does the ascetic Gotama say about this? How does he explain it?"

msgctxt "sn12.24:3.6"
msgid ""
"Kathaṃ byākaramānā ca mayaṃ vuttavādino ceva samaṇassa gotamassa assāma, na "
"ca samaṇaṃ gotamaṃ abhūtena abbhācikkheyyāma, dhammassa cānudhammaṃ "
"byākareyyāma, na ca koci sahadhammiko vādānupāto gārayhaṃ ṭhānaṃ "
"āgaccheyyā”ti?"
msgstr ""
"How should we answer so as to repeat what the ascetic Gotama has said, and "
"not misrepresent him with an untruth? How should we explain in line with his "
"teaching, with no legitimate grounds for rebuke and criticism?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "sn12.24:4.1"
msgid "“Paṭiccasamuppannaṃ kho, āvuso, dukkhaṃ vuttaṃ bhagavatā."
msgstr "“Reverends, the Buddha said that suffering is dependently originated."

msgctxt "sn12.24:4.2"
msgid "Kiṃ paṭicca?"
msgstr "Dependent on what?"

msgctxt "sn12.24:4.3"
msgid "Phassaṃ paṭicca."
msgstr "Dependent on contact."

msgctxt "sn12.24:4.4"
msgid ""
"Iti vadaṃ vuttavādī ceva bhagavato assa, na ca bhagavantaṃ abhūtena "
"abbhācikkheyya, dhammassa cānudhammaṃ byākareyya, na ca koci sahadhammiko "
"vādānupāto gārayhaṃ ṭhānaṃ āgaccheyya."
msgstr ""
"If you said this you would repeat what the Buddha has said, and not "
"misrepresent him with an untruth. You would explain in line with his "
"teaching, and there would be no legitimate grounds for rebuke and criticism."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi2.34"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "sn12.24:5.1"
msgid ""
"Tatrāvuso, ye te samaṇabrāhmaṇā kammavādā sayaṅkataṃ dukkhaṃ paññapenti "
"tadapi phassapaccayā."
msgstr ""
"Consider the ascetics and brahmins who teach the efficacy of deeds. In the "
"case of those who declare that suffering is made by oneself, that’s "
"conditioned by contact."

msgctxt "sn12.24:5.2"
msgid ""
"Yepi te samaṇabrāhmaṇā kammavādā paraṅkataṃ dukkhaṃ paññapenti tadapi "
"phassapaccayā."
msgstr ""
"In the case of those who declare that suffering is made by another, that’s "
"also conditioned by contact."

msgctxt "sn12.24:5.3"
msgid ""
"Yepi te samaṇabrāhmaṇā kammavādā sayaṅkatañca paraṅkatañca dukkhaṃ "
"paññapenti tadapi phassapaccayā."
msgstr ""
"In the case of those who declare that suffering is made by oneself and "
"another, that’s also conditioned by contact."

msgctxt "sn12.24:5.4"
msgid ""
"Yepi te samaṇabrāhmaṇā kammavādā asayaṅkāraṃ aparaṅkāraṃ adhiccasamuppannaṃ "
"dukkhaṃ paññapenti tadapi phassapaccayā."
msgstr ""
"In the case of those who declare that suffering arises by chance, not made "
"by oneself or another, that’s also conditioned by contact."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "sn12.24:6.1"
msgid ""
"Tatrāvuso, ye te samaṇabrāhmaṇā kammavādā sayaṅkataṃ dukkhaṃ paññapenti, te "
"vata aññatra phassā paṭisaṃvedissantīti netaṃ ṭhānaṃ vijjati."
msgstr ""
"Consider the ascetics and brahmins who teach the efficacy of deeds. In the "
"case of those who declare that suffering is made by oneself, it’s impossible "
"that they will experience that without contact."

msgctxt "sn12.24:6.2"
msgid ""
"Yepi te samaṇabrāhmaṇā kammavādā paraṅkataṃ dukkhaṃ paññapenti, te vata "
"aññatra phassā paṭisaṃvedissantīti netaṃ ṭhānaṃ vijjati."
msgstr ""
"In the case of those who declare that suffering is made by another, it’s "
"impossible that they will experience that without contact."

msgctxt "sn12.24:6.3"
msgid ""
"Yepi te samaṇabrāhmaṇā kammavādā sayaṅkatañca paraṅkatañca dukkhaṃ "
"paññapenti, te vata aññatra phassā paṭisaṃvedissantīti netaṃ ṭhānaṃ vijjati."
msgstr ""
"In the case of those who declare that suffering is made by oneself and "
"another, it’s impossible that they will experience that without contact."

msgctxt "sn12.24:6.4"
msgid ""
"Yepi te samaṇabrāhmaṇā kammavādā asayaṅkāraṃ aparaṅkāraṃ adhiccasamuppannaṃ "
"dukkhaṃ paññapenti, te vata aññatra phassā paṭisaṃvedissantīti netaṃ ṭhānaṃ "
"vijjatī”ti."
msgstr ""
"In the case of those who declare that suffering arises by chance, not made "
"by oneself or another, it’s impossible that they will experience that "
"without contact.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "sn12.24:7.1"
msgid ""
"Assosi kho āyasmā ānando āyasmato sāriputtassa tehi aññatitthiyehi "
"paribbājakehi saddhiṃ imaṃ kathāsallāpaṃ."
msgstr ""
"Venerable Ānanda heard this discussion between Venerable Sāriputta and those "
"wanderers who follow other paths."

msgctxt "sn12.24:7.2"
msgid ""
"Atha kho āyasmā ānando rājagahe piṇḍāya caritvā pacchābhattaṃ "
"piṇḍapātapaṭikkanto yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ "
"abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi."
msgstr ""
"Then Ānanda wandered for alms in Rājagaha. After the meal, on his return "
"from alms-round, he went to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side,"

msgctxt "sn12.24:7.3"
msgid ""
"Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā ānando yāvatako āyasmato sāriputtassa tehi "
"aññatitthiyehi paribbājakehi saddhiṃ ahosi kathāsallāpo taṃ sabbaṃ bhagavato "
"ārocesi."
msgstr "and informed the Buddha of all they had discussed."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
msgctxt "sn12.24:8.1"
msgid "“Sādhu sādhu, ānanda, yathā taṃ sāriputto sammā byākaramāno byākareyya."
msgstr "“Good, good, Ānanda! It’s just as Sāriputta has so rightly explained."

msgctxt "sn12.24:8.2"
msgid "Paṭiccasamuppannaṃ kho, ānanda, dukkhaṃ vuttaṃ mayā."
msgstr "I have said that suffering is dependently originated."

msgctxt "sn12.24:8.3"
msgid "Kiṃ paṭicca?"
msgstr "Dependent on what?"

msgctxt "sn12.24:8.4"
msgid "Phassaṃ paṭicca."
msgstr "Dependent on contact."

msgctxt "sn12.24:8.5"
msgid ""
"Iti vadaṃ vuttavādī ceva me assa, na ca maṃ abhūtena abbhācikkheyya, "
"dhammassa cānudhammaṃ byākareyya, na ca koci sahadhammiko vādānupāto "
"gārayhaṃ ṭhānaṃ āgaccheyya."
msgstr ""
"Saying this you would repeat what I have said, and not misrepresent me with "
"an untruth. You would explain in line with my teaching, and there would be "
"no legitimate grounds for rebuke and criticism."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi2.35"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc9"></a>
msgctxt "sn12.24:9.1"
msgid ""
"Tatrānanda, ye te samaṇabrāhmaṇā kammavādā sayaṅkataṃ dukkhaṃ paññapenti "
"tadapi phassapaccayā."
msgstr ""
"Consider the ascetics and brahmins who teach the efficacy of deeds. In the "
"case of those who declare that suffering is made by oneself, that’s "
"conditioned by contact. …"

msgctxt "sn12.24:9.2"
msgid "Yepi te … pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn12.24:9.3"
msgid "yepi te … pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn12.24:9.4"
msgid ""
"yepi te samaṇabrāhmaṇā kammavādā asayaṅkāraṃ aparaṅkāraṃ adhiccasamuppannaṃ "
"dukkhaṃ paññapenti tadapi phassapaccayā."
msgstr ""
"In the case of those who declare that suffering arises by chance, not made "
"by oneself or another, that’s also conditioned by contact."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc10"></a>
msgctxt "sn12.24:10.1"
msgid ""
"Tatrānanda, yepi te samaṇabrāhmaṇā kammavādā sayaṅkataṃ dukkhaṃ paññapenti, "
"te vata aññatra phassā paṭisaṃvedissantīti netaṃ ṭhānaṃ vijjati."
msgstr ""
"In the case of those who declare that suffering is made by oneself, it’s "
"impossible that they will experience that without contact. …"

msgctxt "sn12.24:10.2"
msgid "Yepi te … pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn12.24:10.3"
msgid "yepi te … pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn12.24:10.4"
msgid ""
"yepi te samaṇabrāhmaṇā kammavādā asayaṅkāraṃ aparaṅkāraṃ adhiccasamuppannaṃ "
"dukkhaṃ paññapenti, te vata aññatra phassā paṭisaṃvedissantīti netaṃ ṭhānaṃ "
"vijjati."
msgstr ""
"In the case of those who declare that suffering arises by chance, not made "
"by oneself or another, it’s impossible that they will experience that "
"without contact."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc11"></a>
msgctxt "sn12.24:11.1"
msgid ""
"Ekamidāhaṃ, ānanda, samayaṃ idheva rājagahe viharāmi veḷuvane "
"kalandakanivāpe."
msgstr ""
"Ānanda, this one time I was staying near Rājagaha, in the Bamboo Grove, the "
"squirrels’ feeding ground."

msgctxt "sn12.24:11.2"
msgid ""
"Atha khvāhaṃ, ānanda, pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya rājagahaṃ "
"piṇḍāya pāvisiṃ."
msgstr ""
"Then I robed up in the morning and, taking my bowl and robe, entered "
"Rājagaha for alms."

msgctxt "sn12.24:11.3"
msgid "Tassa mayhaṃ, ānanda, etadahosi:"
msgstr "Then I thought:"

msgctxt "sn12.24:11.4"
msgid "‘atippago kho tāva rājagahe piṇḍāya carituṃ."
msgstr "‘It’s too early to wander for alms in Rājagaha."

msgctxt "sn12.24:11.5"
msgid ""
"Yannūnāhaṃ yena aññatitthiyānaṃ paribbājakānaṃ ārāmo tenupasaṅkameyyan’ti."
msgstr ""
"Why don’t I go to the monastery of the wanderers who follow other paths?’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc12"></a>
msgctxt "sn12.24:12.1"
msgid ""
"Atha khvāhaṃ, ānanda, yena aññatitthiyānaṃ paribbājakānaṃ ārāmo "
"tenupasaṅkamiṃ; upasaṅkamitvā tehi aññatitthiyehi paribbājakehi saddhiṃ "
"sammodiṃ."
msgstr ""
"Then I went to the monastery of the wanderers who follow other paths, and "
"exchanged greetings with the wanderers there."

msgctxt "sn12.24:12.2"
msgid ""
"Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃ. Ekamantaṃ "
"nisinnaṃ kho maṃ, ānanda, te aññatitthiyā paribbājakā etadavocuṃ:"
msgstr ""
"When the greetings and polite conversation were over, I sat down to one "
"side. …”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi2.36"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc13"></a>
msgctxt "sn12.24:13.1"
msgid ""
"‘Santāvuso gotama, eke samaṇabrāhmaṇā kammavādā sayaṅkataṃ dukkhaṃ "
"paññapenti."
msgstr ""
"(The wanderers asked the Buddha the very same questions, and he gave the "
"same answers.)"

msgctxt "sn12.24:13.2"
msgid ""
"Santi panāvuso gotama, eke samaṇabrāhmaṇā kammavādā paraṅkataṃ dukkhaṃ "
"paññapenti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn12.24:13.3"
msgid ""
"Santāvuso gotama, eke samaṇabrāhmaṇā kammavādā sayaṅkatañca paraṅkatañca "
"dukkhaṃ paññapenti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn12.24:13.4"
msgid ""
"Santi panāvuso gotama, eke samaṇabrāhmaṇā kammavādā asayaṅkāraṃ aparaṅkāraṃ "
"adhiccasamuppannaṃ dukkhaṃ paññapenti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn12.24:13.5"
msgid "Idha no āyasmā gotamo kiṃvādī kimakkhāyī?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn12.24:13.6"
msgid ""
"Kathaṃ byākaramānā ca mayaṃ vuttavādino ceva āyasmato gotamassa assāma, na "
"ca āyasmantaṃ gotamaṃ abhūtena abbhācikkheyyāma, dhammassa cānudhammaṃ "
"byākareyyāma, na ca koci sahadhammiko vādānupāto gārayhaṃ ṭhānaṃ "
"āgaccheyyā’ti?"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc14"></a>
msgctxt "sn12.24:14.1"
msgid "Evaṃ vuttāhaṃ, ānanda, te aññatitthiye paribbājake etadavocaṃ:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn12.24:14.2"
msgid "‘paṭiccasamuppannaṃ kho, āvuso, dukkhaṃ vuttaṃ mayā."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn12.24:14.3"
msgid "Kiṃ paṭicca?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn12.24:14.4"
msgid "Phassaṃ paṭicca."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn12.24:14.5"
msgid ""
"Iti vadaṃ vuttavādī ceva me assa, na ca maṃ abhūtena abbhācikkheyya, "
"dhammassa cānudhammaṃ byākareyya, na ca koci sahadhammiko vādānupāto "
"gārayhaṃ ṭhānaṃ āgaccheyyāti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc15"></a>
msgctxt "sn12.24:15.1"
msgid ""
"Tatrāvuso, ye te samaṇabrāhmaṇā kammavādā sayaṅkataṃ dukkhaṃ paññapenti "
"tadapi phassapaccayā."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn12.24:15.2"
msgid "Yepi te … pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn12.24:15.3"
msgid "yepi te … pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn12.24:15.4"
msgid ""
"yepi te samaṇabrāhmaṇā kammavādā asayaṅkāraṃ aparaṅkāraṃ adhiccasamuppannaṃ "
"dukkhaṃ paññapenti tadapi phassapaccayā."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc16"></a>
msgctxt "sn12.24:16.1"
msgid ""
"Tatrāvuso, ye te samaṇabrāhmaṇā kammavādā sayaṅkataṃ dukkhaṃ paññapenti, te "
"vata aññatra phassā paṭisaṃvedissantīti netaṃ ṭhānaṃ vijjati."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn12.24:16.2"
msgid "Yepi te … pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn12.24:16.3"
msgid "yepi te … pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn12.24:16.4"
msgid ""
"yepi te samaṇabrāhmaṇā kammavādā asayaṅkāraṃ aparaṅkāraṃ adhiccasamuppannaṃ "
"dukkhaṃ paññapenti, te vata aññatra phassā paṭisaṃvedissantīti netaṃ ṭhānaṃ "
"vijjatī’”ti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc17"></a>
msgctxt "sn12.24:17.1"
msgid "“Acchariyaṃ bhante, abbhutaṃ bhante."
msgstr "“It’s incredible, sir, it’s amazing,"

msgctxt "sn12.24:17.2"
msgid "Yatra hi nāma ekena padena sabbo attho vutto bhavissati."
msgstr "how the whole meaning is stated with one phrase."

msgctxt "sn12.24:17.3"
msgid ""
"Siyā nu kho, bhante, esevattho vitthārena vuccamāno gambhīro ceva assa "
"gambhīrāvabhāso cā”ti?"
msgstr ""
"Could there be a detailed explanation of this meaning that is both deep and "
"appears deep?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc18"></a>
msgctxt "sn12.24:18.1"
msgid "“Tena hānanda, taññevettha paṭibhātū”ti."
msgstr "“Well then, Ānanda, clarify this matter yourself.”"

msgctxt "sn12.24:18.2"
msgid "“Sace maṃ, bhante, evaṃ puccheyyuṃ:"
msgstr "“Sir, suppose they were to ask me:"

msgctxt "sn12.24:18.3"
msgid ""
"‘jarāmaraṇaṃ, āvuso ānanda, kiṃnidānaṃ kiṃsamudayaṃ kiṃjātikaṃ "
"kiṃpabhavan’ti?"
msgstr ""
"‘Reverend Ānanda, what is the source, origin, birthplace, and root of old "
"age and death?’"

msgctxt "sn12.24:18.4"
msgid "Evaṃ puṭṭhohaṃ, bhante, evaṃ byākareyyaṃ:"
msgstr "I’d answer like this:"

msgctxt "sn12.24:18.5"
msgid ""
"‘jarāmaraṇaṃ kho, āvuso, jātinidānaṃ jātisamudayaṃ jātijātikaṃ "
"jātipabhavan’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘Reverends, rebirth is the source, origin, birthplace, and root of old age "
"and death.’"

msgctxt "sn12.24:18.6"
msgid "Evaṃ puṭṭhohaṃ, bhante, evaṃ byākareyyaṃ."
msgstr "That’s how I’d answer such a question."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi2.37"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc19"></a>
msgctxt "sn12.24:19.1"
msgid "Sace maṃ, bhante, evaṃ puccheyyuṃ:"
msgstr "Suppose they were to ask me:"

msgctxt "sn12.24:19.2"
msgid "‘jāti panāvuso ānanda, kiṃnidānā kiṃsamudayā kiṃjātikā kiṃpabhavā’ti?"
msgstr "‘What is the source of rebirth?’"

msgctxt "sn12.24:19.3"
msgid "Evaṃ puṭṭhohaṃ, bhante, evaṃ byākareyyaṃ:"
msgstr "I’d answer like this:"

msgctxt "sn12.24:19.4"
msgid ""
"‘jāti kho, āvuso, bhavanidānā bhavasamudayā bhavajātikā bhavappabhavā’ti."
msgstr "‘Continued existence is the source of rebirth.’"

msgctxt "sn12.24:19.5"
msgid "Evaṃ puṭṭhohaṃ, bhante, evaṃ byākareyyaṃ."
msgstr "That’s how I’d answer such a question."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc20"></a>
msgctxt "sn12.24:20.1"
msgid "Sace maṃ, bhante, evaṃ puccheyyuṃ:"
msgstr "Suppose they were to ask me:"

msgctxt "sn12.24:20.2"
msgid "‘bhavo panāvuso ānanda, kiṃnidāno kiṃsamudayo kiṃjātiko kiṃpabhavo’ti?"
msgstr "‘What is the source of continued existence?’"

msgctxt "sn12.24:20.3"
msgid "Evaṃ puṭṭhohaṃ, bhante, evaṃ byākareyyaṃ:"
msgstr "I’d answer like this:"

msgctxt "sn12.24:20.4"
msgid ""
"‘bhavo kho, āvuso, upādānanidāno upādānasamudayo upādānajātiko "
"upādānappabhavo’ti."
msgstr "‘Grasping is the source of continued existence.’"

msgctxt "sn12.24:20.5"
msgid "Evaṃ puṭṭhohaṃ, bhante, evaṃ byākareyyaṃ."
msgstr "That’s how I’d answer such a question."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc21"></a>
msgctxt "sn12.24:21.1"
msgid "Sace maṃ, bhante, evaṃ puccheyyuṃ—"
msgstr "Suppose they were to ask me:"

msgctxt "sn12.24:21.2"
msgid "upādānaṃ panāvuso … pe …"
msgstr "‘What is the source of grasping?’ …"

msgctxt "sn12.24:21.3"
msgid "taṇhā panāvuso … pe …"
msgstr "craving …"

msgctxt "sn12.24:21.4"
msgid "vedanā panāvuso … pe …"
msgstr "feeling …"

msgctxt "sn12.24:21.5"
msgid "sace maṃ, bhante, evaṃ puccheyyuṃ:"
msgstr "Suppose they were to ask me:"

msgctxt "sn12.24:21.6"
msgid "‘phasso panāvuso ānanda, kiṃnidāno kiṃsamudayo kiṃjātiko kiṃpabhavo’ti?"
msgstr "‘What is the source of contact?’"

msgctxt "sn12.24:21.7"
msgid "Evaṃ puṭṭhohaṃ, bhante, evaṃ byākareyyaṃ:"
msgstr "I’d answer like this:"

msgctxt "sn12.24:21.8"
msgid ""
"‘phasso kho, āvuso, saḷāyatananidāno saḷāyatanasamudayo saḷāyatanajātiko "
"saḷāyatanappabhavo’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘The six sense fields are the source, origin, birthplace, and root of "
"contact.’"

# Note that MS here punctautes correctly; there is a “ti after the previous statement, and at the end of this section. BB omits this detail, which, admittedly, is odd and doesn” t have an immediate explanation.
msgctxt "sn12.24:21.9"
msgid ""
"‘Channaṃ tveva, āvuso, phassāyatanānaṃ asesavirāganirodhā phassanirodho;"
msgstr ""
"‘When the six sense fields fade away and cease with nothing left over, "
"contact ceases."

msgctxt "sn12.24:21.10"
msgid "phassanirodhā vedanānirodho;"
msgstr "When contact ceases, feeling ceases."

msgctxt "sn12.24:21.11"
msgid "vedanānirodhā taṇhānirodho;"
msgstr "When feeling ceases, craving ceases."

msgctxt "sn12.24:21.12"
msgid "taṇhānirodhā upādānanirodho;"
msgstr "When craving ceases, grasping ceases."

msgctxt "sn12.24:21.13"
msgid "upādānanirodhā bhavanirodho;"
msgstr "When grasping ceases, continued existence ceases."

msgctxt "sn12.24:21.14"
msgid "bhavanirodhā jātinirodho;"
msgstr "When continued existence ceases, rebirth ceases."

msgctxt "sn12.24:21.15"
msgid "jātinirodhā jarāmaraṇaṃ sokaparidevadukkhadomanassupāyāsā nirujjhanti."
msgstr ""
"When rebirth ceases, old age and death, sorrow, lamentation, pain, sadness, "
"and distress cease."

msgctxt "sn12.24:21.16"
msgid "Evametassa kevalassa dukkhakkhandhassa nirodho hotī’ti."
msgstr "That is how this entire mass of suffering ceases.’"

msgctxt "sn12.24:21.17"
msgid "Evaṃ puṭṭhohaṃ, bhante, evaṃ byākareyyan”ti."
msgstr "That’s how I’d answer such a question.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn12.24:21.18"
msgid "Catutthaṃ."
msgstr ""
